BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 738.00 Td (Sensors collect information from the environment. Actuators create motion or physical) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 723.83 Td (action. The controller processes information and chooses commands. Feedback allows the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 709.65 Td (system to compare what is happening with what should happen.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 670.98 Td (For example, a mobile robot navigating a greenhouse may use distance sensors to detect) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 656.80 Td (obstacles, motors to move its wheels, a controller to choose a path, and feedback to correct) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 642.63 Td (its direction.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 603.95 Td (Scene 4: Kinematics and Dynamics) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 556.55 Td (Kinematics describes motion without focusing on the forces that cause it. It helps us answer) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 542.38 Td (questions such as: Where is the robot? How fast is it moving? What path is it following?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 503.70 Td (Dynamics looks at forces, mass, acceleration, torque, and energy. It helps us understand) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 489.53 Td (what effort is required to move a robot safely and efficiently.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 450.85 Td (In early simulation exercises, learners do not need to solve every equation by hand. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 436.68 Td (goal is to understand how motion variables affect behavior and how control strategies can) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 422.50 Td (improve performance.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 383.83 Td (Scene 5: Control and Simulation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 336.43 Td (Control is the process of making a robotic system behave in a desired way.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 297.75 Td (An open-loop system sends commands without checking the result. A closed-loop system uses) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 283.58 Td (feedback to adjust its actions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 244.90 Td (For most practical robots, feedback control is essential. If a robot is expected to move) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 230.73 Td (forward one meter, feedback helps it detect whether it has moved too little, too far, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 216.55 Td (drifted off course.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 177.88 Td (Simulation allows us to test these ideas before using physical hardware. This lowers cost,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 163.70 Td (reduces risk, and helps learners explore mistakes safely.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 125.03 Td (Scene 6: Sustainability Robotics) Tj ET
endstream
